LMDB OPEN test1

LMDB CLEAR

LMDB INFO 

* Insert duplicates + single

LMDB PUT A 1

LMDB PUT A 2

LMDB PUT B 3

LMDB INFO 

* (entries should now be 3 if you’re counting each dup as an entry; LMDB stats vary by how you report)

* Seek duplicates

LMDB SEEK A

* Expected: two lines: A -> 1 and A -> 2

* Scan inclusive range

LMDB SCAN A B

* Expected: A -> 1, A -> 2, B -> 3
* If B doesn’t appear: your scan termination logic is wrong (inclusive bound / compare / break condition).

* Delete one duplicate

LMDB DEL A 2

LMDB SEEK A

* Expected: one line A -> 1
* Close / reopen persistence

LMDB CLOSE

QUIT

* restart dottalkpp

LMDB OPEN test1

LMDB SEEK A (expect A -> 1)

LMDB SEEK B (expect B -> 3)

LMDB SCAN A C (expect A then B)